animal.description: Clef is a truly 'funtastic' dog. He has tons of energy, and loves to play and learn new things. He can be a couch potato at times, but definitely prefers to stay busy! He's a smart pup and has had a ton of training. He knows to 'sit, 'lie down, 'stand, 'back up, 'stay, go to his crate, get his ball, when it's time to 'play' and when it's time for 'din din'. He is eager to learn more of this human language and commands! A typical day with Clef involves several training and game sessions, a walk or two, and him taking naps in between. He loves puzzle toys for when you need to focus on something else, especially if those toys are filled with peanut butter! At the end of the day when he's tired, he'll cuddle with you and ask for belly rubs, and reward you with face licks. If you want him to get excited, just say the word 'play', and he'll dash over to the door with his tail wagging! Clef loves to chase after squirrels and cats, and definitely wishes he had wings so he could chase after birds too. He would thrive in a house without small dogs or other pets. Other dogs would first need to be introduced to him to see if they would be good fits. We don't have much information about how he is with kids, but he has been observed to be nonchalant towards them during walks. He has a habit of dashing out when the door is opened, and needs a home that will make sure to take care that he doesn't get out. Clef would prefer to live in a house with a fenced-in yard, and with people who are home most of the day. He is house-trained and crate-trained, but he's not the type of dog who likes to be left alone for long periods of time because he gets bored and anxious. If you work from home or live with others who do, he would be a great addition to your life! Come meet this energetic boy, he would love to show you how smart he is!

animal.description:
Animal Profile: Mr. Nacho is our longest rescue resident and he has been patiently waiting for his forever home since September 2019. Nacho is a sweet 60 lb male bully breed mix from Kauai. He's about 7 years old, affectionate, and loves to cuddle with his foster family. He's had full obedience training and has excellent leash manners but does require a skilled handler who can provide good leadership. He is currently being fostered with a trainer and his adoption will include two take home lessons. While on leash he can be extremely excitable, but with proper handling he will heel politely by your side. He is crate trained and loves to fetch. Nacho's ideal home will be with a dog-savvy couple or family in a single-family residence outside the city with a securely fenced yard (no apartments), no pets, and no children under the age of 12.

Adoption Info: Adoption fee is $400, which includes spay/neuter, current rabies/DAPPV/bordetella vaccinations, microchip, health certificate, and heartworm test. All adoption fees are donations to a Washington non-profit corporation and all donations go to benefit the animals in our rescue.

Apply online at www.DogGoneSeattle.org

Animal History: This dog was rescued and joined us from Kauai Humane Society rescue partner. He will be available for adoption in Seattle once evaluated.

About Foster to Adopt Program:
Fosters provide a safe landing spot for dogs transitioning from the shelter environment and help prepare the dogs for adoption. You provide the love and structure, and we take care of everything else! We cover all vet care, and drive the adoption process. Average length of foster is 2-3 weeks. Fosters do get first consideration for adoption, if desired.

Apply to foster online at www.doggoneseattle.org/foster-application

animal.description:
Strawberry is approx. 4 year old bull terrier mix.  She weighs just under 40 lbs. She is precious.   She has a great personality.  She is very sweet and is very loving.  She loves to chase balls and play with toys.  She is the typical "small dog syndrome" and tends to overreact to smaller dogs when  she first meets them; however, once she gets to know them, she will do fine.  She's not a fan of cats however.  She knows a few commands.  Like most rescue pups, this furbaby is HW+, but is currently undergoing the *slow-kill method of treatment (see more information below).  

All our adoption fees include spay/neuter, micro-chip, up-to-date vaccinations, including rabies thru date of adoption. This pup is heartworm positive and is currently being treated with the *slow kill method, approved by her veterinarian, on prevention & on flea/tick prevention. 

*The slow kill method of treatment, simply stated, is a 30 day regiment of  doxycycline followed by a monthly dose of Advantage Multi for 12 months, then retesting.   Most dogs test negative after one year of following this treatment; however, we always recommend that potential adopters consult & follow the advice of their family veterinarian upon adopting any of our hw+ pups.   Although the fast-kill method is still considered the "gold-standard" by the AVA, and may be preferred by some vets; the slow-kill method has proven to be effective in our rescue. The main reason we utilize this method is due to our limited financial constraints and the high number of our rescue pups that are infected.   In the cases of severe infection and if the pup is highly symptomatic, we sometimes use the fast-kill approach instead.   Again, we recommend for you to consult with your veterinarian after the adoption is complete and follow their recommendations.   

In order to be considered for one of our beautiful pups, please go to our website and complete and application: https://www.mustluvdogs.org/adoptable-pets.
Please note that we are a DUE DILIGENCE adoption organization. Part of our approval process requires, among other things:
* Experienced pet home with verifiable vet references/history preferred, but we realize that everyone has to start somewhere, so all applications will be considered.
*The majority, but not all, of our pets require a fenced yard or secure enclosure.  In the case of apartments, we require Landlord approval and designated dog area in complex.
*Verifiable good veterinary history INCLUDING regular vaccination/visits and good Heartworm Prevention history is a MUST!
*Adopter must be able to have time to spend with the pup and be able to provide the pup a safe environment to live.
*ALL our dogs are expected to be primarily INSIDE dogs.  They MUST sleep inside the home.  We truly understand that some folks have working dogs (i.e. farmers, ranchers,etc); however, the majority of our dogs have had a rough life prior to coming to us & we want to make sure that they are showered with LUV & maybe even a bit spoiled for the rest of their lives. 

Other facts are also considered, including whether children or other pets are a good fit with the dog. 

Must Luv Dogs reserves the right to deny any applications that we don't think are a good fit with the pup. Our first & foremost concern is the dog's best interest. It is our MISSION to place them in a home that is a great fit for their needs for a lifetime of luv & being part of a family.
*We will consider adoptions in any area; however, will do not ship or transport puppies under the age of 12 mos. We will ONLY transport an adult dog on a transport approved by MLD, at adopter's expense.
* In order to be affordable and afford every family an opportunity to have a pup of their own, we keep our Adoption Fees low; however, please keep in mind that the fees we charge do not cover all costs for the pup.  Any additional donations are greatly appreciated!

Please note that all of our pets are in private foster homes. In order to reduce any stress or confusion for our pups, we require a completed, approved application BEFORE setting up a meet & greet for any of our pups.  Alternatively, you are always welcome to come meet any of our pups at one of our regular Adoption Events.   Our events are always posted on PetFinder OR on our Facebook page: https://www.facebook.com/mustLUVdogs.org.

Finally, THANK YOU for considering Must Luv Dogs for your next pet. 

*Most dogs require a fenced area in yard. 
*Apartments okay IF nearby dog park or walking trails (with landlord appoval).
*ALL dogs must be INSIDE dogs and treated a part of family. 
*We are a DUE DILIGENCE Adoption Rescue.  
*Must have good Vet history & Heartworm prevention is a MUST!
*ALL dogs are fully vetted, spay/neutered and microchipped prior to adoption.

SEAMUS - ID#A044208
Hi! My name is SEAMUS. I am a neutered male, cream Siberian Husky. The shelter staff think I am about 2 years and 8 month old. I have been at the shelter since an Jan 28, 2021.
I LOVE TO: Run around and play in the yard.
I HAVE: A confident and active disposition.
I GET ALONG WELL WITH: Adults and older children.
I WOULD RATHER NOT: Be left alone for long periods of time.
I NEED: Puppy, obedience training and plenty of exercise!
I AM: Friendly and happy!

Starting the Adoption Process

Thank you for your interest in adopting an animal…..to begin the process you will need to access & submit an adoption application. 

You can access our adoption application at either, Petprojectfoundation.org or on the City of San Clemente’s website, under the Animal Services option.  An adoption application can be submitted to the shelter, via Fax at (949) 366-4765, via email to Animalservices@scdpanimalshelter.org, or dropped off at the shelter in the drop box, located by our front door.  The San Clemente – Dana Point Animal Shelter is located at 221 Avenida Fabricante in San Clemente.

We look forward to receiving your application and will be in contact with you via email.

The shelter is currently closed to walk-in public, due to the COVID-19 virus. 

Staff are on site during our regular business hours (below), to address phone calls,  offer shelter services by appointment only, as well as handle any/all animal control concerns.

Our regular business hours are as follows: 

Monday – Closed

Tuesday – 10-4

Wednesday – 10-4

Thursday – 10-4

Friday – 10-4

Saturday – 10-4

Sunday – 12-3

In person services are by appointment only, due to the COVID-19 virus, please contact the shelter at (949) 492-1617, for more information.

Meet Kilo! He's around 7 years old. He's a tall and lean boy who loves people. Kilo would be happiest as the only pet in the home, as he likes getting ALL of the attention. All of our dogs are spayed or neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccinations, microchipped and if over 6 months of age, heartworm tested and on heartworm preventative in their foster home.

We require an approved application to meet any of our dogs. We do not have a shelter location and will not arrange a meeting without an approved application.

We strive to make sure the bios provided for our dogs are complete and accurate; we do understand that mistakes happen, however, so if you absolutely cannot find the answer to your question in the dog's bio, you can contact us for more information.

We require a home visit for each dog we adopt out, so we adopt within a 2 hour radius of Dayton, OH. If you are outside of this radius, we encourage you to contact your local rescue or shelter.

animal.description:
Tiny Madison was brought to the NYC Animal Care Centers as a stray in April 2020.  She was not cared for as she was emaciated and looked like she wasn't cared for. 

Her behavior evaluation came to the conclusion that she was scared, and was acting out, out of fear. Her life was in jeopardy as she was placed on the AT RISK LIST.  

She soon caught the eye of an awesome couple experienced in behavioral dogs and she was placed with them.

She has been learning the ropes and is always a work in progress.

She is approximately 6-7 years old and 40 pounds.  She is good with other dogs as long as they are calm and respectful. She is housebroken, UTD on vaccinations, neutered, and microchipped.

Here is what his foster dad has to say:


We Love Tiny Madison and she has slowly come out of her shell during her stay with us! We have given her a well structured and balanced home that she will need when being adopted, she is still well into her training and when adopted continue with keeping up with it. She is still learning to value human interaction and direction, she is not food motivated but loves praise rewards. We are two experienced dog trainers that will love to keep in contact and help through the transition of her new home. 

Tiny Madison is hand shy, leash shy, lacking in confidence, lacks impulse control, very picky eater, can’t walk for long durations because of hips. Will get separation anxiety if no structure is placed within the home. She does have a heart murmur, so she will need to be kept in a calm household

animal.description:
Thank you for your interest in dog who needs a new home. Adoption can be one of the most fulfilling experiences in your life and especially in the life of your new canine companion.

A note to those looking at CPR. We have no perfect dogs - but many of our dogs have proven to be perfect for a certain someone. Our job is to find those someone's. Our most successful adopters come to CPR not because they want a dog. They come to us because they want to give a dog a home. We urge all of our potential adopters not to fall in love with a picture. While we like to know what you like in looks, a dog is more than a pretty face. Our goal is to match you with the best possible pet for you and your home. We want to create furever families.

Our descriptions contain all that we know about this dog today. We'll update as more information is known.

Are you looking to adopt within the next 30 days? If so please visit our webpage at www.carolinapoodlerescue.org and complete the application. You'll find it in the menu on the left hand side. You'll also find a total listing of all our dogs available.

Just browsing but interested in poodles and poodle mixes? Please drop a note to applications@carolinapoodlerescue.org with your name, address and phone # and email. We'll add you to our mailing list.

thanks
the CPR Adoption team

Date into Rescue: 1/8/2020
Reason for being in rescue: breeder release/puppy who did not sell

Special Needs: David came from a breeder, a puppy who did not sell. He was kennel raised and will need time and patience to learn how to be a pet. David must go to a home with an experienced dog owner. He is not for the first time dog owner. He has behavior quirks that need an experienced dog owner to correct.
Foster location: Dreamweaver Farms, Pacolet SC
Weight: 46 lb
Height: 24 in
Spayed/Neutered: Yes

Adoption Fee: $200

Fence needed? Yes

What kind of home would be best for me? David needs an experienced dog owner and someone who is knowledgeable with training, David has some nipping issues. Its only happening when he gets really excited. He could benefit from another large dog being in the house but doesn't have to have one. David needs a home with high exercise and lots of activities to keep him busy. No children under the age of 18 is a must for him at this time. David needs a lot of structure and routine in his life. He needs training and behavior modification. He gets very stressed and will bark until he is comfortable again.

What is my personality like? David takes some time to warm up, a little longer than most, but once he does he is very energetic and is ready to play! David does have some small nipping issues especially with hands when he gets to excited. He does get a little uneasy when other dogs invade his personal space too much. David is also social with other dogs. He has a large playgroup that he hangs out with everyday and does really well with. He gets stressed in his crate and barks a lot while in there. David will need training and will need full on exercise everyday. David is great with other dogs. It is humans he is very unsure about. David will need time, a lot of time, to fully understand what it means to be a pet. He may never fully make the transition to pampered pooch but we're hoping someone out there with experience and time will see his beautiful face and want to help him try.

How do I act when I first meet new people? Timid and shy, takes time to warm up

Other tips and tidbits: Birthdate 8/30/2018

House trained? Dogs can be house trained if they are in the right environment and are allowed to follow a schedule as long as a physical reason doesn't keep them from being trained. A dog house trained in my home may not be in yours. We will help you teach your new dog this necessary skill and based on your schedule.

Please note - we do not ship dogs. If you are interested in adopting, please take a look at the distance between the foster home location and your location and make sure you are willing to make that trip. Most of our dogs are at our farm in Pacolet, South Carolina.

To apply, please visit our webpage at www.carolinapoodlerescue.org and visit the tab on the left that directions you to the online application.

Please note that when screening applications, we look at the entire home and then make suggestions based on what would be a good fit for your home. You are not being screened for a specific dog although we are looking to see what type of dog interests you - poodles or non poodles, color, age, etc. Others here may be a better fit for you. It is very difficult to get to know a living animal from a picture and a short description. Since we are constantly getting in new dogs, this may be a dog not in our listings yet. We want you to be very happy with your new companion and will make suggestions based on what you tell us about you.

Thank you for considering CPR.

animal.description:
Hey there, I'm Angie. Are you looking for a hiking buddy and a happy camper? I love exploring the outdoors!! My idea of heaven is a day at the river, or out camping in the mountains. I think dog parks are boring and overrated. I may not like other dogs (or cats), but I LOVE people!! I'm chill with all kinds of humans, and I love to hang out with the group.

I've had it rough, but I'm still such a trooper! My humans moved out of our apartment and left me behind when I was full-term pregnant! I was all alone when I gave birth to three puppies without care, food or water. It was days before the local shelter found me and my newborns. By that time, we were all in such bad shape. Sadly, none of my babies survived. I don't let it get me down though, I'm still a great dog and I have such potential in the hands of the right owner!

http://www.wagsandwhiskerspetrescue.com/adopt.html

Thank you so much for looking into wags and whiskers for your next family member.

All of our pets are up to date on vaccinations, microchipped, heartworm tested if over a year old and will be spayed or neutered before being allowed to go home.

Unfortunately, we don't always know the background of each dog. Some were dumped, abandoned in an empty house, left tied to a tree, picked up by animal control as strays, or simply unwanted by their owners. We ask that only serious and committed adopters apply as these dogs have suffered enough.

If you are interested in meeting this pet please apply to adopt at
http://www.wagsandwhiskerspetrescue.com/adopt.html
if the pet is still available for adoption and you are approved to adopt we will contact you.

Calling and checking the status of your application will not increase your chances of adoption

animal.description:
Buddy is a fun loving senior dachshund boy looking to steal your heart. He is about 11 years old and weighs 22 pounds.  Buddy is a small standard boy with personality plus! 

Buddy is an alpha boy who loves to be the boss. He is a a happy fellow and loves to have a belly rub!  Charming and charismatic, Buddy actually chose his own name! His foster mom in Texas called him various days and when she called him Buddy he started coming to it.  Buddy loves to wear a T-shirt (he thinks it makes him look more handsome) 

Buddy gets along well with other dogs but he has not been tested with cats or children, Buddy walks well on a leash and is well mannered. Buddy likes to sleep on the floor on a mat or on cool tiles.  Buddy loves his food and he will complain if it is not on time. He is a very fast eater and his foster mom has a slow feeding bowl for him to slow him down. 

Buddy has a big personality and likes to be the boss. He loves to be petted and loved and talked to! Buddy has quite the response when he is naughty and does something he knows that he shouldn’t - he army crawls with chest on the floor, his butt in the air, and his head tucked down, making his foster mom laugh and laugh. He is a sassy funny happy boy who makes friends wherever he goes! 

Buddy is working on his house training and it is a work in progress with his foster mom helping him learn house manners. Like all dogs that come into rescue, Buddy will take time to adjust to any new home that is lucky enough to welcome him into the family. 

This amazing standard dachshund is going to add love and life to any family he joins with joy and happiness! Apply to adopt Buddy today!

animal.description:
Meet Saskatchewan! 
Or Saska for short. 
She is a 1.5-2 year old Husky mix who loves to play, and run! 

Saska is typically very friendly toward people, and will play with other dogs once she knows them, but tries to boss them around. She has nipped at another dog when it tried to drink out of the same water dish as her, but quickly backed down when she was corrected. 
Saska LOVES to run, and play with toys, if you hand her a stick, she will play with that also! 
Saska has a lot of husky type traits, such as being a runner, and potentially a door dasher if not trained properly. 
She also is not good at this point about coming when you call her, unless you have a toy. 

When Saska came to us she was much to thin, and needed some time to gain weight back, she has done so wonderfully, and at this point is as high of a weight as she could healthily be. ( EST 45-55lbs ) 
She eats about 3.5-4 cups of dog food per day. 

She has no known health issues, other than seemingly having hip dysplasia, which we would encourage you to research before adopting, because she could require some extra care with that as she gets older in age, and should be given the proper supplements, and exercise to help keep her healthy! 
Read more here https://www.akc.org/expert-advice/health/hip-dysplasia-in-dogs/

Saska to our knowledge has not lived in a home with other animals, so we cannot guarantee any of her behaviors with them in a home environment, if you have other pets, you will need to be experienced enough, and comfortable enough to acclimate, and train her around your pets. 
Due to how hyper she tends to be, we would like to see her go to a home with a fully fenced yard for her to play in.
If that is not possible but you can commit the time to taking her for long walks, and exercising her, that is something we can discuss. 

We believe she would do best in a home with children over 13, as she is very hyper, and could easily get out of a gate if left open. 
 


Saska needs some basic training, like walking nicely on a leash, currently she has almost no leash manners, and pulls very hard. 
She will come with a no pull harness, included in her adoption fee. 

She is microchipped, spayed, and current on vaccinations. 

 


If you are interested in this animal,
Please Call us at 435-723-1231 during business hours, we only have one Shelter Technician, so if your phone call is not answered, Leave us a message and we will call you back!

Our Business hours are Tuesday-Friday 10AM-6PM
And Saturday from 9AM-12PM
Or email us at brighamcityanimalshelter@gmail.com anytime.

We are located at 1220 West Forest Street, Brigham City UT, 84302


We are Rescue friendly!
If you are part of a 501C3 Non Profit Organization and would like to Rescue an animal from us if not adopted, PLEASE CONTACT US!

animal.description:
Date of birth 3/27/2018

12/22/2020: Kaiya is a super cute 2 year old Rottweiler! She loves people and is extremely friendly and affectionate. She's super excited to meet new people and she gets all wiggly! She’s a happy, sweet girl.

• Kaiya loves playing with toys— soft toys, rope toys and Kongs! She loves running around the yard with her toys.   

• Kaiya is very smart and treat motivated. She loves peanut butter!  

• She walks nicely on a leash. Our volunteers love to walk her!

• Kaiya needs a home with a fenced yard. She prefers to potty outside in a yard versus when she’s on a leashed walk, although she will sometimes do her business when on a walk. But overall she prefers a little privacy! She was housetrained and crate trained at one time, but we think she'll need a refresher course and may have a few accidents initially. 

• Kaiya can be a little sensitive sometimes about a stranger rubbing her head, neck and shoulders.  Once she knows you, she's fine and enjoys being loved on and she rubs against your legs if you find a good spot to scratch! We’ve done radiographs, including her hips, and can’t see any issues.  She was overweight when she came to us, and we’ve got her down from 94 lbs to 88 lbs now. In addition to losing weight, she's also on a joint supplement (Duralactin) to hopefully help prevent any issues. 

• We’d like to find Kaiya a home with someone who has large dog experience and no young kids. She should be fine with teenagers who are comfortable with large dogs and know how to behave around them. She wouldn’t be a good match for someone who’s never had a dog as an adult.

• Kaiya will most likely need to be the only pet in the home. She was returned to us after being adopted as a puppy because she was not getting along with the other dog in the home. When she’s on a leash walk with other dogs she is usually not reactive and she acts friendly with dogs on the other side of a fence, but she hasn’t done well when we’ve tried to introduce her in the yard. She also needs a home without cats. 

• Kaiya has been spayed, vaccinated, microchipped and tested for heart worms. When she originally came to us as a puppy she had parvo, which she fully recovered from. She’s an absolute sweetheart! 

MORE ON ADOPTING OUR DOGS... 

> COVID-19 UPDATE:  PLEASE SUBMIT AN ONLINE ADOPTION APPLICATION AND A MEMBER OF OUR ADOPTIONS TEAM WILL REACH OUT TO YOU.  Please visit our web site at HSGKC.ORG for an adoption application, our current COVID-19 adoption protocol, and other adoption info.  

> If you decide you'd like to adopt one of the pets you meet, we reserve the pet for you but we generally don't send the pet home with you that day. We’ll instead schedule a pick up date and time that’s convenient for you.   

> Our goal is to send you home with a healthy pet and any information and support you may need to help your new pet adjust to his or her new home.  All of our dogs & puppies have been spayed or neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, treated for fleas & ticks, tested for heartworms (7 mo. and over), and are on monthly heartworm preventative. Puppies who are too young to receive all the necessary puppy boosters and/or first rabies shot may be brought back to us for those vaccines at no extra charge. You will also receive a leash, collar, coupons for pet supplies and services, toys, and educational materials. And we'll give your dog a bath before he or she goes home! 

> Please note that we prefer and may require a fenced yard for many of our dogs.  Exceptions are made on an individual basis depending on the dog's needs, the person's dog experience, the dog's and person's activity levels, home environment and other factors. 

Thank you for searching for a shelter pet!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website. All of our dogs and cats are in foster homes and we have no paid staff. If you have questions concerning a specific animal, PLEASE fill out an application and the foster parent will be in touch. We will not arrange any home visits with any of our dogs and cats until your application is processed. Please understand our foster parents are precious to our 2nd Chance family; without them we cannot function, so we do our best to not burden them with multiple appointments. Our foster parents will choose their top 3 applications and arrange home visits with these applicants. The adopter will be chosen at that time. The process can take anywhere from a week to a month. We want to make sure our little furry ones are placed in their 'forever home' and never have to go through a rehoming again!Hello I was having a rough time where I lived. My mom escaped the abuse and thankfully my mommy said I needed a better life too so I came to 'The Ranch' It is FUN!!! I run in the play yards I can sniff all day and the other dogs are really fun!! Now lets be real. I'm a coonhound so if you are a couch potatoe forget it! I'm smart as a whip and can open doors that have if I really want to. I would be great as a runners pup or agility. I do not like to be in the play yard when mom runs in the house and I will not be good as an only dog I will get bored and in trouble :)I may have a bladder issue that will need surgically corrected but we aren't sure whether it is because I get to busy at the ranch to pay attention to potty breaks or if I really need surgery so when I am adopted we will figure it out and the rescue will have their vet do surgery if necessary.My requirements1. Fenced yard2. Another pup to play withIf you meet my requirements I would LOVE to meet you!! Fill out and application???Please fill out an adoption application:
Adoption application (Dog)
Adoption Application (Cat)

Please understand we do not adopt out dogs to
families with children under the age of 5. We do not adopt dogs to renters. Some dogs will have fence requirements while others may not.

A pet is a lifetime commitment. The dogs and cats in our system find themselves there, for the most part, because their humans did not have the same loyalty to them as they did to their owners. We do not take the adoption process lightly, and will do everything in our power to make sure the animal is placed correctly the first time around for your sake and theirs. Thank you for choosing to adopt not shop!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Lilah has the serious expression of her mother, whom we were told is a Great Pyrenees mixed with Anatolian Shepherd. Lilah has the coat and coloring of a Catahoula or Red Heeler, so we're guessing her dad must be some kind of Cow Dog. But it's all just speculation on our part, and the only way to know for sure which breeds contribute to her unique good looks would be to do a DNA test. That's not in our budget, but if you would like to DONATE one, we would be glad to have it done and share the results. :)

Like most Anatolian Shepherds, Lilah is somewhat reserved, loyal to her family and pack, and distrustful of strangers. This means she doesn't do well at adoption events or even one-on-one in a meet & greet situation, so she gets passed over time and again. But when you win Lilah over, her loyalty to YOU will be unmatched.

Lilah could be a great addition to a small homestead, as she has proven to be safe with our goats, sheep, and chickens. She prefers living inside the house, but goes into the chicken yard with us every day to check things out.

She has been spayed, vaccinated, and microchipped, so she is ready to start protecting your home as soon as you're ready to start earning her trust.

Apply on our website at www.bluebonnetrescue.org.

animal.description:
Hi there! My name is Pearl.  I am a spayed, 5 -6 year old, 50 lb,  Pit/Lab mix..  I have been with my foster family for about 5 months while waiting for my forever family to find me.  Here's what I am looking for in my forever home:

Experience with my breed (Pit bull terrier)

A quiet, calm home with a structured routine and not a lot of people coming and going.  Strangers scare me.

Someone who is home much of the time (I don't like to be alone)

Regular walks and exercise.  I love to play fetch but the dog park is not for me.

A room of my own.  I need a safe space where I can be away from things that make me anxious.  You can have visitors but we will all be happier if I am not forced to interact with them.  No crates please.  They make me feel trapped and I will do my best to escape even if I get hurt in the process.

The opportunity to be the only child.  Having my people all to myself would be blissful.  I like older kids but prefer not to live with the hubbub they can create.
I am selective about my dog friends so I am fine with not having doggie siblings.

An owner who has dog training experience or is willing to work with a trainer to help me feel more relaxed and confident.

I am a very sweet girl. I know I  sound a bit demanding but I will totally make it worth your while.  Snuggling up and keeping you warm while you binge watch TV is one of my specialties.  I know lots of tricks: sit, down, paw and high five. I can snap treats right out of the air when you throw them to me gently.  Did I tell you I love treats?

Up to date on all vaccines, negative for Heartworm and Lyme diseases and microchipped too, I am waiting on pins and needles to meet the love of my life.

If you are interested in finding out more about Pearl, please fill out an application on our website by copying and pasting the following link into your browser:

http://bit.ly/2JnZqK5

Pearl is being fostered in West Springfield and the adoption fee is $300.

"Like" Broken Tail Rescue on Facebook! https://www.facebook.com/brokentailrescue/

NOTE:  Visual breed identification in dogs is unreliable, so for most of the dogs we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each dog as an individual and will do our best to describe each of our dogs based on personality, not by breed label.

We expect that all adopted dogs will enroll in a formal dog training class with their new owners.  Obedience and training classes are an excellent way to learn more about your newly adopted dog, gain handling and training experience, and improve your relationship with your pet.

animal.description:
Courtesy listing.  Please contact us at Deethenetworker@gmail.com

So our 6 year old Beauty is coming back.  Seems she is soulmate with her 12 year old boy but the 6 year old girl is the reason she is coming back.  Apparently there was a growl.  My elegant calm beautiful Dane is grumpy they say.  Here is the old description.

Southern California - We are trying to find foster or permanent home for the remaining 5 of our disaster Danes that came up to us last year from Texas.  Boarding fees are a challenge.  Please share Beauty with friends and family.  The right home is out there.  We just have to find them!  Will consider out of the area homes with home check and appropriate references.

Here is our lovely Beauty.  A big girl, Beauty is coming up on 6 years old later this year.  She is a wonderful companion, great house manners, walks nicely on a lead.  She has had 3 meet and greets and simply great with everyone, but NOT great with other dogs.  She is okay walking by another dog, certainly not interested in running across the street to attack anything.  She is a queen in her mind and that would be peasant behavior.  But Beauty does not care to be sniffed.  Doesn't care for other dogs coming up behind her.  I believe she was attacked at one time and now she is overly cautious.  I spoke with a behaviorist who assessed our Beauty.  It might be possible to correct this response with extreme diligence and training.  But never to be trusted in the company of other dogs without supervision. 

We are looking to place Beauty as the only dog in a household.  Children will be considered over 12 years old provided there is a securely gated front and back yard, 6 feet tall minimum.

This little lady can open gates, not to run away but run to you.  She knows her name, very responsive to verbal recall.  Needs work on obedience commands.  She is housebroken.  

Contact us at Deethenetworker@gmail.com.

animal.description: Hi, My name is Rachel. I am a sweet girl but I am very shy. I am good with other dogs, in fact I love my dog friends! I would love a home with another dog that can show me the way and all that life has to offer. Leash walks are one of my favorites, but please be careful around my collar as I am reactive to my collar being handled and will react if you startle me in that manner. The staff here at BDRR will show you how to leash me up for a walk. Walks are my favorite! I am best suited for an adult only home with another dog for confidence building. I absolutely love attention and love being brushed. I love to cuddle and be treated like a princess. Once I feel comfortable, my true colors come out and all I want to do is give and get affection. I am easy to walk and love to be outside with my human. I love to cuddle up and nap in my bed. Because I am a few years older, I have outgrown all the puppy nonsense and have settled into being a great young dog. I am looking for that special someone to adopt me and give me a forever home.

Sammy is a 2-year-old Labrador/Shar-Pei mix. This boy was picked up as a stray by Animal Control. He had a wound on his shoulder and bilateral entropion eyes. He needed surgery for his eyes so they wouldn't hurt him anymore. Sammy has recovered very nicely from his surgery and his shoulder’s wound has healed.

Sammy is a very vocal dog when he is playing. He's very loving and loves to cuddle. He is good with children but gets a little jealous; he will get between you and anyone or any other dog. He needs room to run and play as he is seeing the world in a whole new light with his eyes that no longer hurt him.

Sammy is house-trained. He weights 50 lb, is fully vetted, neutered, tested heartworm negative and microchipped.

Please visit Regard4Life Animal Rescue at Petsmart in Longview on Saturdays for more information. You can also review our adoption album at http://Regard4Life.org or email regard4life.info@gmail.com.

animal.description:
I know that you will love me and soon you will see, you were meant for me and I was meant for you.  My name is Prior.  I am a 64 lbs, 2 year old, male American Pit Bull mix.  I am a professional at conducting my potty business outside, so house training is no problem.  Although I may require a little coaxing to go in my crate, once I am in there, I am a perfect gentleman.  I have always had the looks and smarts.  But, I wasn’t really sure how to apply all of those smarts.  So, I recently completed a 2 week boot camp.  I learned a lot about control and even left knowing some really sweet commands like, sit, down, stay, leave it and so much more.  Thanks to boot camp, I also learned some really fantastic leash skills.   Most important to me is finding a family that is willing to continue my training so that I can continue to not only be the best dog I can be, but continually get better.  I must admit, I don’t do well with cats, but I would love to have another active dog my size in my home.  Small dogs are too little for me to play with.  Kids are fantastic too.  I would probably do better with older children, but if I find a family with a strong alpha member that continues working on my training, I could easily be a fantastic friend for younger children.  I would do best with a home that has a privacy fenced yard.  As you can see now, it is clear that we are meant for each other, so fill out that application!      

My adoption fee is $150 and includes my spay/neuter, vaccinations, wellness exam, heartworm test, and microchip! If you're interested in meeting/adopting me, please visit www.rescueonespringfield.com/our-adoption-process/adoption-application/ and fill out the form! We do adopt out of state with vet references and video home check. *Adopter is responsible for coming to get the dog and returning the dog if the adoption does not work out* 

Don't forget to LIKE us on Facebook!-www.facebook.com/rescueonespringfield

*Remember, dogs are pack animals. Because of this, Rescue One does not adopt to outdoor-only homes. Pets are family and are not disposable.  Please make sure that you are 100% committed to a pet before considering adding one to your home.

Meet Cora: this gorgeous blonde Lab mix girl is about 2 years old and a petite 45 lbs. She came into our program after being rescued after her family abandoned her. She is a little shy around new people but loving and sweet and affectionate once she gets to know you. She LOVES to swim and can managed stairs off a deck into an above ground pool and would love nothing more that a family with a pool where she is allowed to swim with her people, or play with her family in the pool. animal.description:
Bella is a beautiful 3-year old female Pit Bull Terrier mix who was surrendered by her owner on February 7, 2019.

Bella has a white short smooth coat with patches of black on her right side and hind quarters, a long tail, and an adorable face with a black button nose, short semi-erect ears, and expressive eyes that beg for attention.

This little sweetheart has an affectionate disposition and a rather reserved personality. Bella doesn't rush into a relationship :) She prefers a slow introduction and a little time to get to know you before she turns on her charm. Bella, like many shelter dogs, is completely different outside her kennel so please don't judge her on 'first impressions'.

Bella's current kennel is one of our more open access ones with chain-link fencing on both sides so that she can interact with her neighbors (usually younger dogs and puppies), and Bella is very nice to them.

Her previous owner told us that Bella has been kept indoors and is housebroken. She knows several basic commands (sit, stay, shake, and roll over). Bella has no known behavioral issues.

Bella has an allergy to fleas and must be kept on a good-quality flea treatment to keep her comfortable and also to prevent hair loss.

Bella weighed 46.2 lbs on intake in February 2019 and was already spayed. She appears to have gained a few pounds since then thanks to the gourmet meals our kennel techs serve up each day :)

Bella spent approximately two months in a foster home last summer. She was returned in mid-September 2019 because her foster family moved and there was an unfortunate incident with a door being chewed .. Bella prefers to take the 'Fifth Amendment' and doesn't really want to elaborate about the details :(

These updated photos of Bella were taken on May 28, 2020 when she enjoyed some out-of-kennel time in one of our play yards with volunteer Kathy Wilhelm. Bella has become a favorite of many of our volunteers as well as our kennel techs.

Bella enjoys back scratches, treats, and soft blankets but she doesn’t pursue athletic activities such as playing ball.

Bella is a pushover for back scratches from her people friends and is often treating herself to a back scratch by rolling on her back and kicking all four of her cute paws in the air.  We've shared a video on our Facebook pages of Bella indulging herself for an impromptu back scratch during her photo session on May 28th.

Bella also LOVES blankets and is one happy girl when given a soft blanket that she can 'fluff up' to perfection.

animal.description: Hi, I am Huckleberry (Huck for short) and BDRR rescued me from a Georgia animal shelter. I am a very special boy looking for a special family. I am a large mixed breed weighing in around 65 pounds. I was abandoned and found walking down the middle of the road in Georgia. I am looking for a family who is patient and kind and willing to make me feel loved and secure so I can warm up to new surroundings and friends. I love to take walks, love to nap (they say I'm a terrible snorer), housebroken and crate trained. I adore affection and hugs but I also enjoy a little social distancing without someone in my face. I am protective of my person and home so a family without young children is required. I've joined in on some doggie play groups at the ranch to get to know some of my doggie friends better. Due to my previous circumstances it's going to take me a little time to come out of my shell and trust new people. I know I will thrive with the right family who is willing to put the effort, attention and time into me because I am definitely worth it.

animal.description:
Auggie is seeking a local, adult only home with a fenced yard and a similarly sized playmate!


Auggie is an adorable 2 yr old, 12 lb Pug/Chihuahua mix who was picked up a stray and never reclaimed. He was highly stressed in the shelter and we didn’t hesitate to pull him when his time was up.  This is  Chihuahua personality with the good looks of a Pug. Auggie is a sweet silly boy, a definite lap dog and does expect full furniture privileges.   He loves toys! Auggie likes to play with other similar sized energetic dogs but is intimidated by bigger dogs. Older dogs may not appreciate his enthusiasm. He does okay with a dog savvy cat but for cats not used to dogs he would not be a good fit. Auggie is a resource guarder and because of this he will not be placed in a home with children. He has super sensitive hearing and will protect you from the UPS truck so apartment living is not in his future! Auggie is crate trained and housetrained when on a schedule. He enjoys going for walks and rides in the car. He is neutered, microchipped, vaccinated, HW tested negative and on prevention.


LOCAL INQUIRIES ONLY PLEASE

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Chase is a lovely boy who bonds very quickly with his people. BUT ONLY his people. He can show fear aggression to new people continue into the home.
He just doesn't get comfortable with people other than his immediate handlers .......but he crates well with no problem while visitors are present .
We absolutely adore this lovely boy but he can only be adopted to a home with few visitors because he can show fear aggression to new people in the home.
Over time with consistent training this could improve, and once he learns ' Place' but at this time, the safest way to manage this is to place Chase in a crate or separate room when strangers are present.
His family loved him but did not socialize him well for new people in his home.
He has excellent obedience , is great with dogs and is a fantastic dog ( except for the stranger danger ).
Chase has been diagnosed with hip dysplasia and seen by a top Orthopedic Surgeon ......he is not symptomatic and with some simple exercises ( hill walking )and supplements ( Dasequin) he should continue to run and play with no limitations.

If you are not yet approved to adopt from All Shepherd Rescue, please fill out our online application at www.allshepherdrescue.com. Our adoption fee is $350.00.

animal.description:
Hello everyone! My name is Hartley Rose and I am just the sweetest Pitt Bull Terrier mix! I weigh 40 pounds and more importantly, I love to give kisses. I am potty trained and I don't mind a crate either. I love the dog in my foster home and I love every dog I meet. I would love to have a doggie sibling that I can play with. I have medium energy and pick up on clues when the other dog wants or doesn't want to play. I mostly ignore the cat, sometimes I do get too curious and if you have a kitty in your home, hopefully it's a dog savvy cat. I am working on leash walking, well actually I do know how to do that, I am working on not pulling when I see other dogs or people (I just love them too much). I would love to have a fenced in yard. I still need to get spayed, since I had puppies over the summer. It has been scheduled for the middle of August and then I would love to go to my very own furever family that loves me like I love people.

Yours truly, Hartley Rose.

For inquiries, email inquiry@angelsrescue.org

An Adoption Application for this dog can be found and submitted online at http://www.angelsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-forms

Please be sure to like our Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/angelsrescue.

animal.description:
FAST FACTS:
*Calm Personality
*Cat Friendly
*No Other Dogs
*Older Kids/Teenagers
*Home With a Yard Preferred
*Potty Trained

BIO:
Hi, future family! My name is Shallow, and I am a lovely lady with deep affection for the people who give me the happy life I dream about! I am a beautiful Shar Pei mix - estimated to be about 7 years old and 60 pounds - who is available for adoption through Fetching Tails Foundation. I have some mild arthritis but I don't let that get me down and actually quite enjoy outdoor activities such as boating and dipping my paws in the water with my foster family at their lake house! I would love a grassy yard at my forever home so I can play fetch with my favorite squeaky toy and nap in the sunshine. I enjoy the finer things in life like lounging by your side and enjoying your company (I get along well with everyone I meet!), but I am not a dog who likes hugs and people clinging on me. If you have children, I would do better with older kids/teenagers who understand this. I am cat friendly, but would like to be your only dog because I like your attention on me.

I have excellent manners and make a great roommate. I am potty trained, and can hold it up to 7-8 hours. Because of COVID, my foster family has been home a lot and I haven't been left alone for too long, but when they do need to leave the house I am content to nap and wait for their return. I am a great walking buddy, know a few commands such as sit, come, and lay down, and I don't even beg to get on furniture. If you are looking for an easy-going furry friend who will be happy to join you on outdoors adventures as well as lounge around the house on a lazy weekend, I bet I am the girl for you! I hope you fill out an adoption application soon so we can get out and enjoy the sunny weather!

Love,
Shallow

ADOPTION REQUIREMENTS, NO EXCEPTIONS:
*ADOPTION FEE: $300
*Be at least 21 years of age
*Live in a 50-mile radius of Itasca, within the Illinois border
*Have the knowledge and agreement of all adults living in the household
*Have approval from owner of residence (written in lease)
*Have a valid ID with current address (please provide proof of address if ID address is not up-to-date)
*Be approved as a suitable adoptive home by Fetching Tails Foundation
*Be prepared to make a lifetime commitment

If interested please fill out an application on our website at www.fetchingtailsfoundation.org; please make sure you fill in every required field/question or your submission will not go through. Please note that we take time to learn as much as we can about each dog in our care and our bios are our current observations; we are unable to make any guarantees on the future health or temperament of your adopted dog. Most dogs in our care come with unknown pre-rescue history and as such breed and age estimates are an educated guess.

animal.description:
Hello everyone!  My name is Kenny and am a SUPER handsome stud!

I wound up at the Chula Vista Animal Care Facility because sadly my human family decided they no longer wanted to care for me.  I’m not sure why, since I would never abandon them!  The wonderful people at Passion For Pitties were so kind to pull me from the shelter and now I spend my days with my lovely foster family.  My foster is still getting to know me, but I have settled in quite nicely since arriving home. 


Below is a little bit more about me:

•	I’m approximately 9 years old.
•	Weigh in at a svelte 90 pounds.
•	Overall my demeanor is quite calm and I’m very well behaved.
•	LOVE people and am a crowd favorite whenever I’m out in public!
•	Enjoy nothing more than spending time with my foster family and soaking up their AFFECTION!  I will cry if we are not together.  Who would have thought that a big guy like me would?  
•	GREAT with all dogs, big and small.  However, don’t like it when bigger dogs show aggression towards me.
•	I’m adventurous and always up for a car ride!
•	Going for walks is another favorite activity.
•	Am potty-trained and know some basic commands like “sit” and “down/off.”  Also know “go to bed.”:)


Please help us get sweet Kenny into a safe, loving forever home!  If you're unable to help by adopting, sharing this post or donating is always appreciated.  Don't forget, Passion for Pitties is a 501(c)(3), so all donations are tax-deductible!…every little bit helps!
 
If you would like to adopt our loving dog Kenny, please fill out an application at www.passionforpitties.com under the “Adorable Adoptables” heading.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Soduko Is Ready To Meet You!!

Soduko is looking for his forever and ready to go home! A Shepherd/Retriever mix and just under a year old, he and his sister were abandoned as puppies. When a good Samaritan took them in, she did not realize how full of fear they were. She placed the sister, who promptly fled her new home and planned to take Soduko to the shelter. Fortunately, the stars aligned and that plan resulted in their rescue and Soduko's journey to Labs and Friends.
Soduko began afraid of the world, people, dogs and anything other than his corner. The last several months have been spent working with his foster. She's been teaching him that life can be safe, building confidence and life skills. His foster has brought him this far and he's now looking for his life partner for the next step in his journey.

A wonderful dog with a canvas background painted with his foster and looking for a person to finish the painting with their details together. With a heart eager to please and a lot of smarts the sky is the limit with this boy. Chasing tennis balls around the backyard is his favorite game and he still has that playful puppy attitude. Intellectual stimulation, physical activity and regular training will take far with the person/family who will commit to being HIS forever.

He currently lives with four other dogs and a bird. While eager to interact and play he does not do well with dominant dogs so prefers a playful pup or easy-going mate. He looks to the other dogs for guidance when he's unsure and would thrive with a confident but tolerant housemate. He has learned that the leash is not a death threat but still needs an owner that will help him grow through fear with love and hold on tight when in public so he cannot bolt - someone who will help him continue gaining confidence through life experience. He has learned that the human hand is not always harsh and love can mean attention and affection - especially through a good deep full body massage. His partner will help him meet new people slowly and sit on the grass with him so he can roll over for belly rubs. He would love a home that will love him no matter what and without expectations. Is that you? Please apply and let's meet.

Email dogs@labradorsandfriends.org or fill out our online application at www.labradorsandfriends.org Soduko is located in Southern California.

animal.description:
Meet PeaPod, a fun and outgoing mid sized boy, around 1 1/2 years old, looking for a new home. PeaPod is part of our TBC Guest Dog Program. He is neutered, up to date on vaccinations, crate trained, and gets along well with other dogs. Due to his playfulness, he would probably do best with dogs his size or larger. Besides playing with his fur-friends, PeaPod likes to lounge around the house, and when it's time to go to bed (his crate), he anxiously awaits his nightly treat. We are told that PeaPod does not care for the soft type of treat - he's more of an old fashion dog biscuit kind of guy. This sweet boy has a smile that will melt hearts. He is potty trained, is currently learning how to walk well on a leash, and is definitely treat motivated. To learn more about PeaPod and to add this handsome fella into your family, please complete our pre-adoption application at this link: https://bit.ly/2CCVFPV

animal.description:
Hi! My name is Tyson and I'm 6-years old and a Chow/Boxer Mix. I'm a fun loving fella looking for love! I love to go bye-bye and am a perfect gentleman in the car. I love to go for long strolls and yes, I'm a perfect gentleman on the leash. I'm kinda scared of new men and the HALO people have been working with me. I recently spent the night in a foster home with one of those scary men and after awhile, I realized he wasn't so bad. We went for car rides and walks, played in the yard, and watched basketball together. I also can be a little too reactive to other dogs at times and need to be introduced properly (that's what my HALO people tell me). They say I've been doing a really good job in playgroups and I have made a few dog friends that I am fond of. I am sooooo ready to find my person so I can stroll, go bye-bye, and lounge on the couch with them. Oh, and I'm pretty darn good-looking! If you'd like to meet me, I'd love to meet you so fill out an adoption application and let's do this! Love and kisses, Tyson

We are a foster based organization and DO NOT have our adoptable pets at HALO. You must complete an adoption application to meet the cat or dog. We are by appointment ONLY.

Adoption application: www.halok9behavior.com/forms

animal.description:
Benedict

Located in the Dallas-ish TX area
Male
1-3 years old
House trained we believe but hard to know for sure in boarding
Energetic
Very friendly and social with humans
Has done great with the dogs they he's met in his home but the dogs he encounters on walks he's not a fan of
Should feed separately just because food reactivity is common
Up to date on vaccines
Need to be altered and get his entropians fixed

Benedict and his 2 sisters were surrendered to Garland when they were already slammed. They were at high risk and so we pulled them and put them in boarding for a few days. The foster went to get 2 but loved them all and couldn't leave one behind so she took all 3. The foster he is in now also has his 2 sisters and another dog and he needs more time and attention then this home allows. As a result he's frustrated and taken to jumping the fence and going on adventures. He doesn't have issues with his sisters or the dogs in the home but is reactive when see's dogs on walks or on his adventures. He was dog friendly so I really think it's environmental. He just needs a foster through neuter and eye surgery and then he will transport up to us!

animal.description:
Meet stunning Blue!  He’s a 1.5 years old big fluffy baby, a gorgeous boy around 60lbs! 
As a teenage young pup, Blue can be gentle and loving, but also stubborn and demanding. He could benefit from some obedience training to learn better matters, but he does sit for treats and take them gently! 
Blue craves human love and attention, is a big love bug, likes to jump up on you offering big hugs and kisses, and demanding to sleep next to you like a baby, a gentle sweet angel. However, there’s another side of Blue, he can very mischievous and stubborn, demanding the way he wants, becomes temperamental, so he needs discipline, and boundaries. Blue is very playful, needs lots of daily exercise and mental stimulation, or can be a trouble maker. He definitely needs an experienced northern breeds dog owner to be his leader, who understands the breed, sets rule and boundaries for him to follow. Definitely no young kids are recommended for Blue. 
Blue loves other dogs of his size, both males and females, and seems submissive towards dogs older than he is, so it is highly recommended for Blue to become part of a pack in a home with other big dog(s), especially the alpha older ones as a good role models for him, to put him in place, and to keep him occupied to avoid the boredom of being the only dog. 

Blue has been neutered, microchipped and current on vaccines. Please email us if interested, alljoy4paws@yahoo.com

Blue is currently in Northern California, Sacramento area.

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Sulley, and I was rescued by Cuz i Matter Animal Rescue on 8/14/2019.  I am a "bait dog" survivor of a horrible dog fighting past, who came in with extensive injuries, a bullet lodged in my rib cage, multiple abrasions and cuts as well as missing a "digit" and numerous toe nail injuries to where I am still limping while my paws heel.  The injuries were so severe, that I was told I would not have survived had it not been for CiMAR saving me and getting me to a Vet for the needed care before placing me into a wonderful Foster Home.  I am healing up great, though I still have a limp, but I love playing outside with my new canine friends.

Sulley is the sweetest dog, no trouble at all, loves to be near you at all times.  Loves the attention that he probably never got before.  Super gentle with the other dogs, and loves to play with any dog that comes his way.

If you'd like more information about me, please send CiMAR an email so they can send you all the information about adopting me.  You can also find more pictures of me on their website:  http://www.cuzimatter.org/adopt-a-dog

animal.description:
Location: New Orleans, Louisiana 

Diamond was a owner surrender to a shelter north of New Orleans. Cane Haven Rescue pulled her from the shelter to give her another chance at life. Diamond is approximately 3 years old, up to date on vaccinations, spayed & microchipped. 

Diamond has had a very rough past. When she came into rescue she had an embedded collar, several open wounds and scars. We do not know what her life was like before rescue, but we know that she will never have to worry again. Since her past is unknown, her potential adopters must give her time to settle in. A meet and greet with any other pets is an absolute must. 

Diamond is house trained, kennel trained & knows her basic commands/manners. 

Interested adopters can fill out an application at canehavenrescue.com. 
Any possible questions about Diamond, please email canehavenrescue@gmail.com 

Cane Haven Rescue will transport any of their adoptable dogs to the right home. We do require adoption fees that are based on the age & health status of the adoptable dog. The adoption fee covers every single dog in CHR with vaccinations, heartworm test, deworming, microchip, spay/neuter & medications. All CHR adoptable dogs are current on their monthly  heartworm and flea medication. A CHR representative will do a home check to ensure the pets are placed in a secure and loving home. 

www.canehavenrescue.com

Location: Colorado Springs, Colorado 

Artie was a owner surrender to Cane Haven Rescue. We wanted to give him another chance at life. Artie is approximately 3 years old, up to date on vaccinations, neutered & microchipped. 

Artie has has a tough life and has suffered trauma from it. When he was only 4 weeks old, he was taken away from his litter and became an outside dog. He was shoved in an outside kennel only big enough for him to stand and lay. He was adopted into a family and they unfortunately needed to surrender him. CHR fell in love with Artie and wanted to make sure he had a positive future. He would do best in a home with older children or children who can understand boundaries. Artie unfortunately can not be around other pets due to his past of other dogs attacking him. We do have a trainer working with Artie through his issues and will help acclimate him into his new loving home. 

Artie is house trained, kennel trained & knows his basic commands/manners.

Hi there! My name is Wookie and I am approximately 6 years old. I came to the SPCA a long time ago when my owner was going into the hospital. I was soon adopted, but I became protective of my new Mom and I was later returned to the SPCA. 

Not many dogs here are made for outdoor life, but I have told staff I would be very happy as an indoor OR an outdoor dog. I appear to be housebroken, I know some of my commands, and I love to play fetch. But, I prefer to be the only animal in the home and I am not recommended for a family with children. 

I just know there is the perfect home out there for me... is it with you?
Love, Wookie

Alex is looking for a BEST friend. She's okay in a small family with or without dogs. She's an adventurer and water lover. She requires extra mental stimulation or she will be bored. Loves sights and sounds. Very gentle. Old dog in a puppy body! Loves kisses. More so independent than clingy 

Nicky wants a large family with or without other dogs. She wants a lot of excitement and attention. Loves to jump. Might not be suitable for homes with old / cranky dogs. Loves hammock time and chasing the hose. More so clingy than independent 

Puppy adoptions require a matchmaking quiz prior to adoption. Adoptions start as a 30 day foster period in which the puppy May be pulled if it is not the right fit home. 
If you are interested in a puppy, you must contact me with the personality of dog you are ideally looking for. ie loyal, playful, calm, brave, dopey, etc 
These are wonderful puppies. And they will only go to homes that will promise them a FOREVER. 

Please visit Linktr.ee/lcpitbullrescue 
Fill out the FOSTER APPLICATION
And MATCHMAKING QUIZ 
I will contact you after evaluating them.

animal.description: Lupen is a one year old who gets along great with other dogs and loves to wrestle and play. He knows how to sit and lay down. He is fearful of new people but with the right person who is willing to be patient with him, he will be your best friend. Unfortunately he is more fearful of men. However once he learns to trust as he has with his fosters brother, he will reciprocate. From his foster mom: "Lupen is a complete goofball. Belly rubs are his favorite kind of love, and hes more than happy to curl up in bed with you. If you dont mind, he will thank you with lots of kisses and wet willies. He has lots of energy so he will do best with someone willing to play with him on a daily basis" Lupen is currently living with a 10-year-old girl so we feel he will do well with or without kids in the home. He is crate-trained and does best when he has a toy to entertain him. Lupen has not been cat tested, but he is interested in birds in his yard. His current foster says he is a sweet little guy and has made great progress in their home. We are looking for a family that will be patient and living to Lupen and has another dog in the home as a companion.

animal.description: Charlie is such an easygoing dude when he's hanging out in the house. He can be reluctant to meet new humans, but once he's properly introduced to them, he becomes their comfortable buddy - a happy and snuggly homebody. He's so exuberant when he sees the people he knows and loves. This lively boy is excited to exercise, and he loves going for walks, jogs, and runs with his foster. animal.description:
Please DO NOT send an email to us from the PetFinder CONTACT button. It will delay any correspondence getting to us.

Email TenderHeartRescue2@gmail.com for adoption information and our adoption schedule. Email is the best form of communication for us and will receive a quicker response than phone calls. Our volunteers work full time jobs in addition to rescue, so please be patient. Thank you!

If interested in any of our dogs please complete our on-line pre-adoption application AND our Great Pyr questionnaire (if interested in a Pyr) at www.tenderheartrescue.webs.com on the main page.

We do require that you have a pet/vet history which means you must have owned a dog (past and/or current) and your pets must be current on vetting which includes spay/neuter, vaccines and heart worm test/prevention.

Rescue related phone calls will NOT be returned until after 7pm. If you do call, please ensure that you are calling from the number you wish to be contacted at and that your number is not blocked.

We typically do not do OUT OF STATE adoptions.

Our dogs are spayed/neutered, have been given age appropriate vaccines and are microchipped.

animal.description:
REQUIREMENTS:
* detached single-family home with fenced yard
* home outside the city
* herding dog experience
* quiet home without a lot of activity or new visitors
* Texas has trust issues and needs a rescue experienced home - please indicate your rescue experience on the application
* He can bite when he feels mistrust
* if a dog in the current home,  should be about his size or a little larger

Say hello to 3 year old Texas, aka Tex, our sweet young adult Australian Shepherd mix. He is ready to find his home in the PNW.  He's about 55lb. 

Tex is true to his herding breed traits and requires a herding dog experienced family. He is super sweet with his people but can be wary of strangers, so he would do best in a calm household with not a lot of new people coming and going. He can also be strong headed and will benefit from a family that can give him structure and expectations. He is smart and loves treats.

He does well with other dogs and loves to play out in our play yard with his dog friends. He does not appreciate super pushy or dominate large dogs but will give them a warning if he isn't a fan of their behavior. Texas is a rough and tumble kind of dog that likes to wrestle. We do not recommend him in a home with cats.  

Tex requires an adult only home, no kids, out of the city with a fully fenced yard. No apartments for him. He would do great having another young active dog to play with in the home. 

Texas is UTD on his shots, microchipped and neutered. His adoption fee is $450.

animal.description:
Why did the blind dog cross the road? Because she couldn't see what was on the other side! Ha-ha, get it?! A blind dog can't see! I am SO silly! And I'm blind, but that obviously doesn't hamper my ability to be happy and have fun, I just bump into things sometimes. My playing skills are top notch, almost as good as my snuggling skills! And if you combine those two you'll understand how I'm such a good wrestler with my dog friends. I'm also super talkative, so you can be sure I'll tell you what I'm thinking! Like how I caught Valley Fever when I was younger and need to take meds for the rest of my life, but nowadays I'm doing amazing! I'm like a little caterpillar who had to work really hard to survive and now I've transformed into this beautiful, strong butterfly who is ready for her own home. If you're ready for a chatty, sassy, and snuggly best friend, contact Mayday to tell them you'd like to adopt the pretty little butterfly!

If you, or someone you know, are interested in adopting or fostering, please visit our site at www.maydaypitbullrescue.org or send us an email at info@maydaypitbullrescue.org

Please contact us at Deethenetworker@gmail.com

May 22 Update 

I have spent time every day with this pair.  The boy is more wary at first but infinitely more affectionate once he trusts you.  The girl is easier to make friends with but she doesn't give gentle kisses like the boy.  She can be silly, he can be a clown.  Both have lived with young children but the boy needs room to be and open space, stimulation.  Both are capable of killing a coyote or a strange dog.  Both are instinctual guardians.  They will not allow a stranger to enter their territory.  And did I mention hair????

Los Angeles - These beauties, Tibetan Mastiffs, were well loved and life circumstances require this brother and sister find homes either separately or together.  They have not been living together very long.  

Both dogs go home altered, microchipped, heartworm and tick disease screen, blood and chemistry, dental, vaccinated, dewormed, groomed.  Please be experienced with the breed.  I would prefer opposite sex placement with one other dog.  Placements and any specialized care supervised by breed enthusiasts every step of the way.

Basil is a full sized pup who is 50 lbs and has the most stunning brown eyes! She is always ready for action and has a zeal for living life to the fullest!  She has touched our hearts and makes us smile and laugh every day.   She loves to snuggle on the couch with us (both humans and canines).  She is so easy to entertain, as she loves bones, toys, and chews of all shapes and sizes.  Outside, she will jump high in the air in attempt to catch her toys.  She often misses and tumbles to the ground, but nothing stops this girl.  She just keeps on going!

She is crate trained, house broken, and is near fluent in basic obedience (still working on refining a few puppy manners- she just gets so excited about life).  She knows many tricks and is easily motivated by food, toys, and lovings.  She loves running and wrestling with her foster siblings, hiking, running, and walking.  She has the cutest and softest snore when she is worn out from a big day.  She is the sweetest pup.

Basil is a brave warrior who has overcome many obstacles. Her scars paint a sad story, but she is ready to tackle any obstacles head on. She has learned what all the strange noises and moving parts to a house are and that the lawn mower is not actually evil. When new people come over, she barks and can be hesitant, but positive reinforcement has helped her feel safe and loved by newcomers. We are also still working on some puppy manners, but she loves training (especially for stella and chewy treats)!

In her dream home, Basil would be the only  dog or would have a tolerant and well socialized doggie playmate who will be able to handle her exuberant play style and can continue to teach her about all the fun there is to be a dog. She prefers to be in an adult only home (or a home with  older kids).

I love this girl like one of my own and will provide free continued training to help her with a smooth transition into her final forever home. (I am a certified dog trainer.)  I promise you won't regret being patient with her as she adjusts, as she is such a sweet girl with a lifetime of snuggles and kisses to give! :)

Please apply on our website www.fourleggedranch.com
Feel free to reach out with questions about Basil to her foster mom directly at 317-696-8479.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Go big or go home, that's my motto! I'm Dax, and I'm all in when it comes to most things in life, especially playing and napping. I like to run, romp, and chase things in the backyard. Then I'll power down for a good snuggle session on the couch. I'll do almost anything for a treat or a Kong filled with peanut butter, especially show you one of my favorite tricks - sit, stay, and shake. Do you love hugs? Great! I give the best, biggest hugs!

I can be picky with my canine friends and sometimes I get so excited that I forget how big I am, so I may do best in a home without other dogs or with more laid-back pups. I also need to live in a home without cats or younger kiddos. Don't worry - I'm crate trained, but also responsible when given free rein of the house. I'm just looking for a forever home where I can relax and be with my people!

I also am not the most polite pup on leash yet and since I'm a BIG boy, that can be a lot for someone to handle. I get worked up when I see other dogs, which is because I am just overly excited but it comes off as not very nice. So due to that, I need an adopter who has some strong arms, a strong core, and a lot of love and patience to help me learn better leash manners. I don't think I'd do well in an apartment since I'd be walking past lots of other dogs in that environment, which may be stressful for you and me both. I would love a nice backyard!

Are you ready to go all in with me? Email my friends at PawsCo at adopt@pawscoadoptions.org or visit this information page: pawsco.org/adopt/adoption-process to fill out an application.Our adoption process is:

1. Fill out our Adoption Application online. We'll contact you within 48 hours to answer any questions you may have about the pet.

2. If the pet looks like a great match, we'll schedule a meet and greet and ask you to fill out our online Adoption Agreement if you'd like to proceed with adopting. Once you've completed the Adoption Agreement and pay the pet's Adoption Fee, you can arrange to pick up your new furry family member!

animal.description:
Tiny is a giant puppy. He is about 95 pounds and a young full grown dog. Tiny is a Rhodesian ridgeback without the ridge. Tiny needs a fenced yard. He is a car chaser and can be very distracted. He does not know his own size. 
 
Tiny also needs someone who feels comfortable handling and training a very large dog. While he is big, he is sensitive and will not do well with any harsh training methods. He is very playful. It is his youthfulness that makes him act like a puppy. He will soon grow out of this. He is very laid back and well behaved. He is learning how to sit and stay. He is food motivated and loves to sit for a treat.  

He is friendly and good with other dogs. He doesn't understand when other dogs are intimidated by him. He is very naïve and would not do well with a male dog who is triggered by him. He has lived with male and female dogs large and small and done very well. Tiny has not had any accidents in the house. 

Tiny was treated for heartworms. Because he is a young dog, he will likely have no long-term effects, as he isn't old enough to have had them very long. 

If you are interested in Tiny, fill out a pre-adoption application. It can be found on our website or on the page that accompanies this description. This is the best way to start the conversation about adopting Tiny. We will take applications until we find a good match for Tiny.  If he is still on here, he is available.
